                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2131½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-28T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 28, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Your 19, January 24, 5 p.m. The Department has been informed by the British
                    Embassy here that all exports originating in Syria, Turkey or other countries to
                    which the British control system has been extended must be covered by
                    certificates of origin, in order to assure non-interference, regardless of
                    whether the goods are loaded at Basra or elsewhere and regardless of whether
                    they are carried on American or other vessels. The American Eastern Corporation
                    informs the Department that American vessels loading at Basra are requiring
                    certificates of origin for cargoes originating in such countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
